## Creating an Array

Think of an Array as a cargo train. It is a single variable, but it has multiple "cars" hitched together, each holding a different piece of data.

We create arrays using **Square Brackets `[]`**, separating items with commas.

```javascript
// A single variable holding THREE strings!
let heroes = ["Batman", "Superman", "Wonder Woman"];

// Arrays can hold any data type!
let highScores = [1500, 1000, 850, 400];
```

## Changing the Paint

Arrays are totally mutable, meaning you can change the contents inside the train cars *after* you build the array.

If you want to replace Batman with Spider-Man, you simply overwrite that specific index using the `=` sign:

```javascript
let heroes = ["Batman", "Superman", "Wonder Woman"];

// Overwrite Index 0
heroes[0] = "Spider-Man"; 

console.log(heroes);
// Outputs: ["Spider-Man", "Superman", "Wonder Woman"]
```

You just changed the data inside the first slot!
